---
layout: base.njk
metaTitle: "Calculators — RURR Advisors"
description: "Free SIP and investment return calculators from RURR Advisors — model step-up SIPs, varying return scenarios, and partial withdrawals. For illustration only."
---
<section class="page active" id="page-calculators">
  <div class="page-head">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="crumb reveal">Tools</p>
      <h1 class="reveal">Calculators</h1>
      <p class="reveal">Model how disciplined investing can compound over time. Switch between an SIP growth projection and side-by-side return scenarios. These are planning aids, not predictions.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section wrap">
    <div class="note reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
      <strong>For illustration only.</strong> The return figures you enter are assumptions, not forecasts — actual returns vary and are <strong>not guaranteed</strong>. Investments in securities and mutual funds are subject to market risks. Nothing here constitutes investment advice or a promise of returns.
    </div>

    <!-- ============ CALCULATOR TOGGLE ============ -->
    <div class="calc-switch reveal" id="calcSwitch" role="tablist" aria-label="Choose a calculator">
      <button class="calc-tab is-active" id="tab-sip"  type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="true"  aria-controls="sipCalc"  data-target="sipCalc">SIP growth</button>
      <button class="calc-tab"           id="tab-lump" type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="lumpCalc" data-target="lumpCalc">Lumpsum</button>
      <button class="calc-tab"           id="tab-goal" type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="goalCalc" data-target="goalCalc">Goal planner</button>
      <button class="calc-tab"           id="tab-swp"  type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="swpCalc"  data-target="swpCalc">Retirement &amp; SWP</button>
      <button class="calc-tab"           id="tab-ret"  type="button" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="retCalc"  data-target="retCalc">Return scenarios</button>
      <span class="calc-tab-ind" aria-hidden="true"></span>
    </div>

    <!-- ============ SIP CALCULATOR ============ -->
    <article class="calc" id="sipCalc" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-sip">
      <div class="calc-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">SIP Calculator</p>
        <h2>What your monthly SIP could grow to.</h2>
        <p class="calc-sub">Add an optional annual step-up and a partial withdrawal to model a more realistic plan.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="calc-grid">
        <form class="calc-inputs" id="sipForm" autocomplete="off">
          <div class="field">
            <label for="sipAmount">Monthly investment (₹)</label>
            <input type="number" id="sipAmount" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="500" value="10000">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="sipReturn">Expected return (% per year)</label>
            <input type="number" id="sipReturn" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="12">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="sipYears">Investment period (years)</label>
            <input type="number" id="sipYears" inputmode="numeric" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="15">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="sipStepup">Annual step-up (%) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="sipStepup" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="50" step="1" value="0">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="sipWithdraw">Partial withdrawal (₹ per year) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="sipWithdraw" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="1000" value="0">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="sipWithdrawStart">Withdrawals start after (years) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="sipWithdrawStart" inputmode="numeric" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="10">
          </div>
        </form>

        <div class="calc-result" id="sipResult" aria-live="polite">
          <p class="calc-result-label">Estimated value at maturity</p>
          <p class="calc-figure" id="sipMaturity">—</p>
          <dl class="calc-rows">
            <div class="calc-row"><dt>Total invested</dt><dd id="sipInvested">—</dd></div>
            <div class="calc-row" id="sipWithdrawnRow" hidden><dt>Total withdrawn</dt><dd id="sipWithdrawn">—</dd></div>
            <div class="calc-row"><dt>Wealth gain</dt><dd id="sipGain">—</dd></div>
          </dl>
          <p class="calc-foot">Assumes monthly investing and monthly compounding at the rate you entered. Step-up applies once a year.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- ============ LUMPSUM CALCULATOR ============ -->
    <article class="calc" id="lumpCalc" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-lump" hidden>
      <div class="calc-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Lumpsum Calculator</p>
        <h2>What a one-time investment could grow to.</h2>
        <p class="calc-sub">See how a single upfront investment compounds over time at your assumed rate of return.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="calc-grid">
        <form class="calc-inputs" id="lumpForm" autocomplete="off">
          <div class="field">
            <label for="lumpAmount">Investment amount (₹)</label>
            <input type="number" id="lumpAmount" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="10000" value="500000">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="lumpReturn">Expected return (% per year)</label>
            <input type="number" id="lumpReturn" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="12">
          </div>
          <div class="field calc-field-3">
            <label for="lumpYears">Investment period (years)</label>
            <input type="number" id="lumpYears" inputmode="numeric" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="10">
          </div>
        </form>
        <div class="calc-result" id="lumpResult" aria-live="polite">
          <p class="calc-result-label">Estimated value at maturity</p>
          <p class="calc-figure" id="lumpMaturity">—</p>
          <dl class="calc-rows">
            <div class="calc-row"><dt>Amount invested</dt><dd id="lumpInvested">—</dd></div>
            <div class="calc-row"><dt>Wealth gain</dt><dd id="lumpGain">—</dd></div>
          </dl>
          <p class="calc-foot">Assumes monthly compounding at the rate you entered. A one-time investment with no further contributions.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- ============ GOAL PLANNER ============ -->
    <article class="calc" id="goalCalc" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-goal" hidden>
      <div class="calc-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Goal Planner</p>
        <h2>How much to invest for a goal.</h2>
        <p class="calc-sub">Set a target and a timeframe to find the monthly SIP it takes, optionally adjusted for inflation and money you've already saved.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="calc-grid">
        <form class="calc-inputs" id="goalForm" autocomplete="off">
          <div class="field">
            <label for="goalTarget">Goal amount in today's money (₹)</label>
            <input type="number" id="goalTarget" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="50000" value="2000000">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="goalYears">Years to goal</label>
            <input type="number" id="goalYears" inputmode="numeric" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="10">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="goalReturn">Expected return (% per year)</label>
            <input type="number" id="goalReturn" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="12">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="goalInfl">Goal inflation (% per year) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="goalInfl" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="20" step="0.5" value="6">
          </div>
          <div class="field calc-field-3">
            <label for="goalCurrent">Already saved for this goal (₹) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="goalCurrent" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="10000" value="0">
          </div>
        </form>
        <div class="calc-result" id="goalResult" aria-live="polite">
          <p class="calc-result-label">Monthly SIP required</p>
          <p class="calc-figure" id="goalSip">—</p>
          <dl class="calc-rows">
            <div class="calc-row"><dt>Goal in today's money</dt><dd id="goalToday">—</dd></div>
            <div class="calc-row" id="goalFutureRow"><dt>Goal after inflation</dt><dd id="goalFuture">—</dd></div>
            <div class="calc-row"><dt>You'll invest in total</dt><dd id="goalInvested">—</dd></div>
          </dl>
          <p class="calc-foot" id="goalFoot">Assumes monthly investing with monthly compounding. Inflation grows the goal's future cost.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- ============ RETIREMENT & SWP ============ -->
    <article class="calc" id="swpCalc" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-swp" hidden>
      <div class="calc-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Retirement &amp; SWP</p>
        <h2>Build a corpus, then draw an income.</h2>
        <p class="calc-sub">Grow a retirement corpus with a monthly SIP, then see how long it can fund a monthly withdrawal (SWP) once you retire.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="calc-grid">
        <form class="calc-inputs" id="swpForm" autocomplete="off">
          <div class="field">
            <label for="swpYears">Years to retirement</label>
            <input type="number" id="swpYears" inputmode="numeric" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="20">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="swpSip">Monthly SIP now (₹)</label>
            <input type="number" id="swpSip" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="500" value="15000">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="swpPre">Return before retirement (% per year)</label>
            <input type="number" id="swpPre" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="12">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="swpCurrent">Current corpus (₹) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="swpCurrent" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="10000" value="0">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="swpWithdraw">Monthly income in retirement (₹)</label>
            <input type="number" id="swpWithdraw" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="1000" value="60000">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="swpPost">Return after retirement (% per year)</label>
            <input type="number" id="swpPost" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="8">
          </div>
        </form>
        <div class="calc-result" id="swpResult" aria-live="polite">
          <p class="calc-result-label">Corpus at retirement</p>
          <p class="calc-figure" id="swpCorpus">—</p>
          <dl class="calc-rows">
            <div class="calc-row"><dt>Monthly income drawn</dt><dd id="swpIncomeEcho">—</dd></div>
            <div class="calc-row"><dt>That income lasts</dt><dd id="swpLasts">—</dd></div>
          </dl>
          <p class="calc-foot">Accumulation uses monthly compounding. In retirement, the corpus earns the post-retirement rate while you withdraw monthly. The withdrawal is constant (not inflation-indexed).</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- ============ RETURN CALCULATOR ============ -->
    <article class="calc" id="retCalc" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-ret" hidden>
      <div class="calc-head">
        <p class="eyebrow">Return Calculator</p>
        <h2>The same plan under different return assumptions.</h2>
        <p class="calc-sub">Combine a lumpsum and an SIP, then compare conservative, moderate, and aggressive outcomes side by side.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="calc-grid">
        <form class="calc-inputs" id="retForm" autocomplete="off">
          <div class="field">
            <label for="retLump">Initial lumpsum (₹) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="retLump" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="10000" value="100000">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="retSip">Monthly SIP (₹) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="retSip" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="500" value="10000">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="retYears">Period (years)</label>
            <input type="number" id="retYears" inputmode="numeric" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="15">
          </div>
          <div class="field calc-field-3">
            <label>Return scenarios (% per year)</label>
            <div class="calc-trio">
              <span><small>Conservative</small><input type="number" id="retLow" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="8"></span>
              <span><small>Moderate</small><input type="number" id="retMid" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="10"></span>
              <span><small>Aggressive</small><input type="number" id="retHigh" inputmode="decimal" min="0" max="40" step="0.5" value="12"></span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="retWithdraw">Partial withdrawal (₹ per year) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="retWithdraw" inputmode="numeric" min="0" step="1000" value="0">
          </div>
          <div class="field">
            <label for="retWithdrawStart">Withdrawals start after (years) <span class="opt">optional</span></label>
            <input type="number" id="retWithdrawStart" inputmode="numeric" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="10">
          </div>
        </form>

        <div class="calc-result" id="retResult" aria-live="polite">
          <table class="data-table calc-table">
            <caption>Projected maturity value</caption>
            <thead>
              <tr><th>Scenario</th><th>Return</th><th>Maturity value</th></tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody id="retTableBody">
              <tr><td>Conservative</td><td class="num" id="retLowPct">—</td><td class="num" id="retLowVal">—</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Moderate</td><td class="num" id="retMidPct">—</td><td class="num" id="retMidVal">—</td></tr>
              <tr><td>Aggressive</td><td class="num" id="retHighPct">—</td><td class="num" id="retHighVal">—</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <dl class="calc-rows">
            <div class="calc-row"><dt>Total invested</dt><dd id="retInvested">—</dd></div>
            <div class="calc-row" id="retWithdrawnRow" hidden><dt>Total withdrawn</dt><dd id="retWithdrawn">—</dd></div>
          </dl>
          <p class="calc-foot">The lumpsum is invested at the start; the SIP is added monthly. All amounts compound monthly at each scenario's rate.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <div class="section wrap" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="cta-band reveal">
      <h2>Numbers are a start. A plan is the rest.</h2>
      <p>A calculator can't profile your risk, your goals, or your taxes. Let's turn these projections into a written, personalised plan.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contact/">Schedule a consultation</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/services/">See all services</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
